```java
@SpringBootApplication
public class SpringBootApp {

    @Autowired
    private RabbitTemplate rabbitTemplate;

    // Declare queue and routing key
    public static final String QUEUE_NAME = "myqueue";
    public static final String ROUTING_KEY = "myroutingkey";

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SpringApplication.run(SpringBootApp.class, args);
    }

    @PostConstruct
    public void sendMessage() {
        // Declare exchange
        rabbitTemplate.setExchange("myexchange");

        // Declare queue and binding
        Queue queue = new Queue(QUEUE_NAME, true, false, false);
        DirectExchange exchange = new DirectExchange("myexchange");
        Binding binding = BindingBuilder.bind(queue).to(exchange).with(ROUTING_KEY);
        rabbitTemplate.execute(channel -> {
            channel.queueDeclare(QUEUE_NAME, true, false, false, null);
            channel.exchangeDeclare("myexchange", "direct", true);
            channel.queueBind(QUEUE_NAME, "myexchange", ROUTING_KEY);
            return null;
        });

        // Send message to queue with mandatory flag set to true to receive acknowledgement
        rabbitTemplate.convertAndSend(QUEUE_NAME, ROUTING_KEY, "Hello from Spring Boot!", message -> {
            message.getMessageProperties().setDeliveryMode(MessageDeliveryMode.PERSISTENT);
            message.getMessageProperties().setPriority(0);
            message.getMessageProperties().setContentType("text/plain");
            message.getMessageProperties().setHeader("key", "value");
            message.getMessageProperties().setExpiration("10000");
            message.getMessageProperties().setMandatory(true);
            return message;
        });
    }
}
```
In this updated example, the queue and routing key declaration have been moved to the Spring Boot application. The queue is declared with the properties of being durable, non-exclusive, and non-auto-delete. The exchange and binding are also declared in the sendMessage() method. The message is sent with the mandatory flag set to true to receive an acknowledgement from the message receiver. The message properties can also be set as needed.

Note that this is just one possible implementation and the configuration can be adjusted based on the specific requirements of the application.

